it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:138:- Bad native-image skip:\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:25:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. New-library metadata must be provided through `reachability-metadata.json`, including any test-only metadata under `tests/src/**`.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:97:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\nforge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:20:    - If GRAALVM_HOME is set and contains bin/native-image, use it for both GRAALVM_HOME and JAVA_HOME.\nforge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:21:    - Else, if JAVA_HOME is set and contains bin/native-image, use it for both GRAALVM_HOME and JAVA_HOME.\nforge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:26:        native_image_path = os.path.join(home, \"bin\", \"native-image\")\nforge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:42:        \"ERROR: Unable to locate a GraalVM Java home with native-image. \"\nforge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:43:        \"Please set GRAALVM_HOME or JAVA_HOME to a GraalVM distribution where bin/native-image exists.\"\nforge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:49:    \"\"\"Return True when the provided GraalVM home contains native-image.\"\"\"\nforge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:50:    native_image_path = os.path.join(home, \"bin\", \"native-image\")\nforge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:55:    \"\"\"Require a GraalVM home environment variable that contains native-image.\"\"\"\nforge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:63:            f\"where {os.path.join('bin', 'native-image')} exists.\",\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:3:description: Fix missing GraalVM reachability metadata for a specific library. Use when the user asks to fix or add metadata because required metadata is missing and tests or native-image runs fail with missing metadata errors.\n./skills/README.md:34:### `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`\n./skills/README.md:36:Reviews pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label.\n./skills/README.md:37:It covers native-image runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: verify the native path is fixed rather than skipped, keep metadata and test changes scoped, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\nforge/utility_scripts/metadata_index.py:14:NOT_FOR_NATIVE_IMAGE_FIELD = \"not-for-native-image\"\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:2:name: review-fixes-native-image-run-fail\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:7:# Review `fixes-native-image-run-fail` PRs\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:15:- Confirm the PR has label `fixes-native-image-run-fail`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept fixes that hide the failing native path by skipping assertions, skipping native-image runtime execution, or weakening the test until the failure disappears.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:22:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:29:   - Confirm the PR has label `fixes-native-image-run-fail`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:47:3. Review the native-image fix.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:73:   - Expected minimum: native-image compile and native test execution are green for the target coordinate.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:82:- The PR is scoped to the target existing library and the native-image runtime failure it fixes.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:83:- The native-image runtime path still executes meaningful library behavior.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:86:- Required metadata, Java, native-image compile, and native-image run checks are green.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:94:- CI failures indicate the native-image runtime problem is not actually fixed.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:109:- For native skips: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For unrelated changes: say the PR should stay scoped to the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` repair and remove unrelated files.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Native-image execution should remain enabled by default when the repaired test reaches the native lane. Do not accept changes that skip or short-circuit native-image behavior. When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally relies on open-ended dynamic class loading that native image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, accept the `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` catch pattern from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`. Reject raw native-only skips, bare `catch (Error)` blocks, and use of this pattern for ordinary reflection, resources, serialization, dynamic proxies, JNI, or missing reachability metadata.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:23:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:45:   - Reject or request changes if the PR removes tests, disables test classes, catches and ignores the failing exception, or disables native-image behavior.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:91:- The fix disables native-image behavior instead of using the `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` catch pattern for unsupported open-ended dynamic class loading.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:130:- Bad native-image skip:\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Native-image execution should remain enabled by default when the repaired test reaches the native lane. Do not accept changes that skip or short-circuit native-image behavior. When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally relies on open-ended dynamic class loading that native image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, accept the `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` catch pattern from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`. Reject raw native-only skips, bare `catch (Error)` blocks, and use of this pattern for ordinary reflection, resources, serialization, dynamic proxies, JNI, or missing reachability metadata.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:23:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:45:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:46:   - Reject or request changes if the PR removes tests, disables test classes, catches and ignores the failing exception, or disables native-image behavior.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:77:   - 